<messaging:emailTemplate subject="You have a new CONTRACT approval request: {!relatedto.Name}, {!relatedto.ASI_TH_CRM_Outlet__r.name} {!relatedto.ASI_TH_CRM_Outlet__r.ASI_KOR_Customer_Code__c}" recipientType="User" relatedToType="ASI_TH_CRM_Contract__c"><messaging:htmlEmailBody >    You have a new CONTRACT approval request, the details are as follows:<br/><br/>        Contracr Number: {!relatedto.Name}<br/>    Start Date: <apex:outputtext value="{!relatedto.ASI_TH_CRM_Start_Date__c} "/><br/>    End Date: <apex:outputtext value="{!relatedto.ASI_TH_CRM_End_Date__c} "/><br/>    No. of Months: {!relatedto.ASI_CRM_MO_No_of_Months__c}<br/>    Version No.: {!relatedto.ASI_CRM_Version__c}<br/>     Raised Date: <apex:outputtext value="{!relatedto.LastModifiedDate} "/><br/>     Total Investment Base Value: HKD {!relatedto.ASI_CRM_Total_Investment_Base__c}<br/>     Total Fixed Investment Base Value: HKD {!relatedto.ASI_CRM_Total_Fixed_Inv_Base__c}<br/>     Total Variable Investment Base Value: HKD {!relatedto.ASI_CRM_Total_Variable_Inv_Base__c}<br/><br/>    <c:ASI_CRM_MO_ContractEmail_Cmpnt ContractId="{!relatedto.id}"/>        Details: <a href="{!LEFT($Api.Partner_Server_URL_140, FIND(".com/",$Api.Partner_Server_URL_140)+3)}/{!relatedto.id}">{!LEFT($Api.Partner_Server_URL_140, FIND(".com/",$Api.Partner_Server_URL_140)+3)}/{!relatedto.id}</a>    <br/>        Note: For salesforce.com to process your response the word APPROVE, APPROVED, YES, REJECT, REJECTED, or NO must be in the very first line of the reply email. Also, any comment must be in the second line.</messaging:htmlEmailBody></messaging:emailTemplate>